description: The United States is millions of homes short of demand, and lacks enough affordable housing units. And many Americans feel like housing costs are eating up too much of their take-home pay.
title: Housing experts say there just aren't enough homes in the U.S.

description: The Federal Trade Commission has voted to ban employment agreements that typically prevent workers from leaving their companies for competitors, or starting competing businesses of their own.
title: U.S. bans noncompete agreements for nearly all jobs

description: "I'm not playing with persona," St. Vincent says of All Born Screaming. "It's a really a record about life and death and love. That's it. That's all we got."
title: St. Vincent offers tension, release and sonic 'jump scares'

description: PEN America has cancelled its annual Literary Awards ceremony after nearly half of the authors nominated withdrew in protest over the organization's response to the Israeli-Hamas war in Gaza.
title: PEN America cancels awards ceremony after writers protest
